{"word":"ἄποικος","slug":"ἄποικος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄποικος</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>away from home</i>, <el>ἀπ. πέμπειν τινὰ γῆς</el> to send <i>away from</i> one's country, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a settler, colonist</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἄποικος</el> (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>πόλις</el>), <i>a colony</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}